This paper focuses on deep learning model compression, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with deep learning models and their optimization. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning in the compression process suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
